over our heads

10:34.434 --> 10:37.836
and food on the table.

10:37.838 --> 10:41.272
All I asked was for a little
help taking care of your sister.

10:44.011 --> 10:45.710
Sofe?

10:45.712 --> 10:49.247
I know things have been
rough since your dad died.

10:49.249 --> 10:52.183
I just...

10:52.185 --> 10:56.221
I just need a little time to
get us back on our feet, okay?

11:38.632 --> 11:41.433
Wow, I can't believe somebody
actually rented that place.

11:41.435 --> 11:42.567
Mom!

11:52.846 --> 11:54.579
Christ.

11:54.581 --> 11:56.281
Are you okay?

11:56.283 --> 11:58.283
Yeah, I'm fine.

12:34.654 --> 12:35.720
Whoo!

13:11.992 --> 13:13.625
Amelia.

13:27.340 --> 13:28.673
Well.

13:28.675 --> 13:32.110
Guess St. Stephen's
has the day off.

13:45.225 --> 13:48.693
Murphy,
when did you get hot?

13:58.371 --> 14:00.238
What are you up to?

14:08.381 --> 14:09.681
Whoa.

14:19.593 --> 14:23.194
Amelia, what would you like
for dinner?

14:27.567 --> 14:30.902
I thought Mom was coming home.

14:30.904 --> 14:34.472
She called.
She has to work.

14:34.474 --> 14:38.743
But that's okay because
we can do something special,

14:38.745 --> 14:41.312
just you and me.

14:41.314 --> 14:43.348
What do you say?

14:45.652 --> 14:48.786
Hey, is something wrong?

14:50.457 --> 14:53.591
You're lucky you don't
have to go to school.

14:53.593 --> 14:55.894
Did something happen?
Amelia!

15:11.645 --> 15:13.011
I don't even understand

15:13.013 --> 15:15.513
why they're bothering
with a memorial.

15:15.515 --> 15:17.515
I mean, if Teresa
actually had friends,

15:17.517 --> 15:19.550
